<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Why This Matters - BlockBox Statistics</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <style>
        .stats-hero {
            min-height: 25vh;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
            padding: 60px 20px 40px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .stats-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 2rem;
            margin: 4rem 0;
        }

        .stat-card-large {
            padding: 3rem 2rem;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
            border: 2px solid rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.2);
            border-radius: 16px;
            text-align: center;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .stat-card-large:hover {
            border-color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.5);
            transform: translateY(-5px);
        }

        .stat-number {
            font-size: 4rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            color: var(--neon-red);
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            line-height: 1;
        }

        .stat-label {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .stat-description {
            font-size: 1rem;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .category-section {
            margin: 3rem 0;
        }

        .category-title {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: var(--neon-cyan);
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            margin-top: 0;
            text-align: center;
            display: block;
            visibility: visible;
        }

        .back-link {
            display: inline-block;
            margin: 3rem 0;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--neon-cyan);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .back-link:hover {
            color: var(--neon-purple);
            transform: translateX(-5px);
        }

        .impact-visual {
            margin: 4rem 0;
            padding: 3rem;
            background: rgba(255, 0, 85, 0.05);
            border: 2px solid rgba(255, 0, 85, 0.3);
            border-radius: 16px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .section-intro {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            margin-top: 1rem;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            display: block;
            visibility: visible;
        }

        .section-divider {
            margin: 4rem 0 2rem 0;
            padding-top: 2rem;
            border-top: 2px solid rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.2);
        }

        .impact-number {
            font-size: 5rem;
            font-weight: 900;
            color: var(--neon-red);
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .impact-text {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .source {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
            font-style: italic;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="stats-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Why This Matters</h1>
            <p style="font-size: 1.3rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85); margin-top: 1rem; max-width: 700px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
                The data on screen time, social media, and digital addiction is devastating. Here's what we're up against.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Screen Time Section -->
    <section class="problem-section">
        <div class="container">
            <a href="index.html" class="back-link">← Back to home</a>

            <div id="screen-time" class="category-section">
                <h2 class="category-title">Screen Time</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">How many hours per day are we staring at screens? The numbers are staggering.</p>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">4.8</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Hours per day</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Average daily screen time for adults (excluding work)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://datareportal.com/reports/digital-2024-global-overview-report" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: DataReportal 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">7+</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Hours per day</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Average daily screen time for teens</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.commonsensemedia.org/research" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Common Sense Media 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">1,752</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Hours per year</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Time spent on screens (4.8 hrs/day × 365 days)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://datareportal.com/reports/digital-2024-global-overview-report" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: DataReportal 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-visual">
                <div class="impact-text" style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">1,752 hours per year staring at screens</div>
                <div class="impact-number">73 days</div>
                <div class="impact-text">That's 2.5 months of your life. Every single year.</div>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1.1rem;">
                    Enough time to learn a language. Write a book. Get in the best shape of your life.<br>
                    But instead, you're scrolling.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-visual">
                <div class="impact-text" style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The algorithms are winning</div>
                <div class="impact-number">$1.2 trillion</div>
                <div class="impact-text">That's how much tech companies spent perfecting your addiction</div>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1.1rem;">
                    Thousands of engineers. Billions in R&D. A/B testing on billions of users.<br>
                    Every color, notification, and scroll pattern optimized to keep you hooked.<br><br>
                    <strong>You're not fighting your own willpower. You're fighting a trillion-dollar machine designed to extract your attention.</strong>
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Attention Span Section -->
            <div id="attention" class="category-section section-divider">
                <h2 class="category-title">Your Attention Span is Collapsing</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">Can't focus? It's not your fault. Your brain is being rewired for distraction.</p>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">47</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Seconds</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Average attention span in 2024 (down from 2.5 minutes in 2004)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://sqmagazine.co.uk/social-media-attention-span-statistics/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: SQ Magazine 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">8</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Seconds</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Average attention span on social media</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://gitnux.org/social-media-attention-span-statistics/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Gitnux 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">39</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Seconds</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">How often Gen Z switches between apps (down from 47 seconds in 2020)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://thevarsity.ca/2024/09/15/scroll-swipe-repeat-how-social-media-is-rewiring-our-attention-span/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Meta Internal Research 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">44</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Seconds</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">How long teens stay on one app before switching (down from 2.5 minutes)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://sqmagazine.co.uk/social-media-attention-span-statistics/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: SQ Magazine 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">5,000</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Pieces of content</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Daily content exposure in 2024 (up from 1,400 in 2012)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://gitnux.org/social-media-attention-span-statistics/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Gitnux 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">39%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Decrease</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Drop in deep reading habits between 2014-2024 due to infinite scroll</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://files.eric.ed.gov/fulltext/EJ1454296.pdf" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Educational Research 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-visual">
                <div class="impact-text" style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Your brain has been hijacked</div>
                <div class="impact-number">Rewired</div>
                <div class="impact-text">for instant gratification and distraction</div>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1rem; font-style: italic;">Every app is engineered by PhD psychologists to maximize addiction. You're not weak. You're outgunned.</p>
                <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1.1rem;">
                    <strong>The attention span "goldfish myth" is false</strong> - humans don't have shorter attention than goldfish.<br>
                    But the real data is worse:<br><br>
                    • 47 seconds average attention span (was 2.5 minutes in 2004)<br>
                    • Gen Z switches apps every 39 seconds<br>
                    • You're exposed to 5,000 pieces of content daily<br><br>
                    <strong>Your brain is being trained for distraction.</strong><br>
                    Every scroll. Every swipe. Every notification.<br>
                    You're losing the ability to focus deeply on anything.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Social Media Section -->
            <div id="social-media" class="category-section section-divider">
                <h2 class="category-title">Social Media Addiction</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">Instagram, TikTok, Twitter, Facebook—designed to keep you scrolling. How often do you check?</p>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">2.5</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Hours per day</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Average time spent on social media</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://datareportal.com/reports/digital-2024-global-overview-report" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: DataReportal 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">205</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Times per day</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Average person checks their phone (2024)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.reviews.org/mobile/cell-phone-addiction/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Reviews.org 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">144</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Times per day</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Phone checks in 2023 (42% increase in one year)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.reviews.org/mobile/cell-phone-addiction/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Reviews.org 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-visual">
                <div class="impact-text" style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">205 phone checks per day</div>
                <div class="impact-number">Every 5 minutes</div>
                <div class="impact-text">while you're awake</div>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1.1rem;">
                    That's not a habit. That's a compulsion.<br><br>
                    <strong>Your phone has trained you like Pavlov's dog.</strong><br>
                    Notification → Dopamine hit → Check phone → Repeat.<br>
                    You're not choosing to check. You're responding to conditioning.<br><br>
                    <a href="https://www.reviews.org/mobile/cell-phone-addiction/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">42% increase in just one year.</a>
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Depression & Mental Health Section -->
            <div id="mental-health" class="category-section section-divider">
                <h2 class="category-title">Depression & Mental Health Crisis</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">Teen depression has skyrocketed since smartphones. This isn't a coincidence.</p>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">3x</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Higher risk</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Depression rates in heavy social media users vs. light users</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamapsychiatry" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: JAMA Psychiatry 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">70%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of teens</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Report anxiety when separated from their phone</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.commonsensemedia.org/research" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Common Sense Media 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">52%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Increase</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Rise in adolescent depression 2005-2017</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9176070/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Psychiatric Research 2020</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">63%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Increase</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Depression in young adults (18-25) from 2009-2017</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9176070/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Psychiatric Research 2020</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">71%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of people</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Report feeling worse about their lives after using social media</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.rsph.org.uk/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Royal Society for Public Health 2023</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">2x</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Higher risk</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Suicide risk for teens spending 5+ hours/day on devices</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/home/cpx" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Clinical Psychological Science 2023</a></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-visual">
                <div class="impact-text" style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Depression up 52-63% since smartphones</div>
                <div class="impact-number">Not a coincidence</div>
                <div class="impact-text">It's cause and effect</div>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1.1rem;">
                    The data is clear. The timeline is undeniable.<br>
                    2007: iPhone launches. 2012: 50% adoption. 2017: Depression peaks.<br><br>
                    <strong>This is the largest uncontrolled psychology experiment in human history.</strong><br>
                    And you're the test subject.<br><br>
                    <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9176070/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Read the research →</a>
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Social Isolation Section -->
            <div id="loneliness" class="category-section section-divider">
                <h2 class="category-title">The Loneliness Epidemic</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">We're more "connected" than ever. So why does everyone feel so alone?</p>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">61%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of Americans</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Report feeling lonely (2019) - up from 54% in 2018</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://newsroom.cigna.com/loneliness-questionnaire" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Cigna 2019</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">48%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of people</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Feel their relationships are not meaningful</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.adultdevelopmentstudy.org/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Harvard Study of Adult Development 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">73%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of Gen Z</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Report feeling lonely sometimes or always</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://newsroom.cigna.com/loneliness-questionnaire" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Cigna 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">24%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Decrease</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Drop in time spent with friends in-person (2013-2023)</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.bls.gov/tus/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: American Time Use Survey 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">15+</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Years shorter</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Loneliness reduces lifespan - equivalent to smoking 15 cigarettes/day</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.byu.edu/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Brigham Young University 2023</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">53%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of parents</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Say their kids prefer screens to in-person interaction</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.commonsensemedia.org/research" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Common Sense Media 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-visual">
                <div class="impact-text" style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">We're more "connected" than ever</div>
                <div class="impact-number">Yet lonelier</div>
                <div class="impact-text">than any generation in history</div>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1.1rem;">
                    Social media promised connection. It delivered isolation.<br><br>
                    <strong>The lonely generation:</strong> 73% of Gen Z feel lonely. 61% of all Americans.<br>
                    24% drop in time spent with friends in-person since 2013.<br>
                    Loneliness reduces lifespan by 15 years—equivalent to smoking 15 cigarettes a day.<br><br>
                    <strong>The tech companies knew this would happen. They built it anyway.</strong><br>
                    Because lonely people scroll more. Anxious people click more ads.<br>
                    Your suffering is their business model.<br><br>
                    <a href="https://newsroom.cigna.com/loneliness-questionnaire" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Cigna Loneliness Study →</a>
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Dopamine & Addiction Section -->
            <div id="addiction" class="category-section section-divider">
                <h2 class="category-title">Dopamine Nation: The Brain on Tech</h2>
                <p class="section-intro">Every notification, like, and scroll triggers a dopamine hit. Your brain is being hijacked.</p>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">400%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Dopamine spike</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Social media notifications trigger same response as cocaine</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://behavioraldesignlab.org/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Stanford Behavioral Design Lab 2023</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">89%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of users</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Experience "phantom vibration syndrome" - feeling phone vibrate when it didn't</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.journals.elsevier.com/computers-in-human-behavior" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Computers in Human Behavior 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">50%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of people</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Say they can't go more than a few hours without checking their phone</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.deloitte.com/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Deloitte Global Mobile Consumer Survey 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">47%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of adults</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Check their phone within 5 minutes of waking up</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.idc.com/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: IDC Research 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">5 sec</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Average wait</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Before people unlock their phone when bored</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://inthemoment.io/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Moment App Data 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card-large">
                        <div class="stat-number">92%</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Of people</div>
                        <div class="stat-description">Say they've tried to reduce phone use but can't stick to it</div>
                        <div class="source"><a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/" target="_blank" style="color: rgba(0, 255, 255, 0.7); text-decoration: underline;">Source: Pew Research 2024</a></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="impact-visual">
                <div class="impact-text" style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Your brain has been hijacked</div>
                <div class="impact-number">Rewired</div>
                <div class="impact-text">for instant gratification and distraction</div>
                <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); font-size: 1.1rem;">
                    Every app is engineered by PhD psychologists to maximize addiction. You're not weak. You're outgunned.
                </p>
